<span id="freeTextContainer12778153668129957358">Warning: Reading this book will make you hungry and give you weird cravings for foie gras and asparagus and maybe caviar. She just makes it sound <i>so good</i>. <br/>This is an interesting and engaging look at one woman&apos;s experience as a food critic for the New York Times. She talks about the food she ate, disguises she used, and lessons she learned along the way. I found it funny, charming, and thought-provoking. <br/>I would go 5-stars except that it has taken me 3 tries to get through this one. My first reac</span>
  <span id="freeText12778153668129957358" style="display:none">Warning: Reading this book will make you hungry and give you weird cravings for foie gras and asparagus and maybe caviar. She just makes it sound <i>so good</i>. <br />This is an interesting and engaging look at one woman's experience as a food critic for the New York Times. She talks about the food she ate, disguises she used, and lessons she learned along the way. I found it funny, charming, and thought-provoking. <br />I would go 5-stars except that it has taken me 3 tries to get through this one. My first reaction to her writing style was that it was a tad...off, but I really think it is just her distinct style. It will get in your head. <br />Now excuse me as I return to my cold frozen pizza and dream of brussels sprouts and perfect steak.</span>
